#### The Shorter Poems

### Proverbs

<span id="an_1"></span> What shul these clothes thus manyfold,  
<span id="an_2"></span> Lo this hote somers day?  
<span id="an_3"></span> After grete hete cometh cold;  
<span id="an_4"></span> No man caste his pilche away.  
<span id="an_5"></span> Of al this world the large compas  
<span id="an_6"></span> Yt wil not in myn armes tweyne;  
<span id="an_7"></span> Who so mochel wol embrace,  
<span id="an_8"></span> Litel therof he shal distreyne.  

